KG name: Hua Hin Health Tourism Data Set
Description: We  design the ontology  of health tourism data in Hua Hin and Cha-am.    We focus on the health tourism where one of the popular kinds is the spa service. International SPA Association (ISPA) has divided spa services into six kinds : club spa- day spa- destination spa- medical spa- mineral springs spa and resort/hotel spa. In our prototype area- namely- Hua-Hin- there are four kinds. In this work we design the ontology focused on these four categories.•	Hotel and resort spa: a spa located within a resort or hotel providing wellness components.•	Destination spa: a facility with the main purpose is guided individual spa-goers to develop their healthy habits. •	Day spa: a spa offers to clients a variety of professionally administered spa services on a day-use basis.•	Medical spa: a spa poses an on-site source of natural mineral- thermal or seawater used in hydrotherapy treatments.Please use this to cite our data set:Choksuchat- C.; Ngamphak- S.; Maneesaeng- B.; Chiwpreechar- Y.; Chantrapornchai- C.- "Parallel health tourism information extraction and ontology storage-" Computer Science and Software Engineering (JCSSE)- 2014 11th International Joint Conference on - vol.- no.- pp.236-241- 14-16 May 2014doi: 10.1109/JCSSE.2014.6841873
Authors: Name: chantana chantrapornchai; chidchanok choksuchat; Email:fengcnc@ku.ac.th; cchoksuchat@hotmail.com
